My older daughter enjoys this game although one of the few issues is that when she wants to trace the path for the turtle to go (number count), you have to push really hard on the screen and it has to be directly in the center of the number disc.  Other connect-the-dot applications are easier to do, so I'll have to give this 4 out of 5 for now.  Beyond that small annoyance, it's another great educational application from Thup.

My 4 yr old daughter played this for the first time today and went from not recognizing any numbers to in no time recognizing all numbers from 1-10! Wow - very impressive. Held her attention for ages, as she wanted to keep adding to her aquarium - so that does work as a great reward/incentive. So much so actually, that my 7 year old son, after seeing hers, insisted I put it on his Nexus 7 too (they both just got one each for Christmas). So I installed it on his, as well as Monkey Word School (which is a bit more his level educationally), and the kids compared aquariums/terrariums all afternoon (although admittedly, a lot of the other app was a bit too challenging for my girl). Would love to see even more activities added to this app, and the other just to ensure it keeps there interest... because unfortunately most educational apps don't for long. But so far, so good!
